        "content": "<p>CarePlan.activity.detail.location is a Reference(Location). <br>\nIn some cases this is too much. We just have to say \"do it at home\".<br>\n<span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"191403\">@Michelle (Moseman) Miller</span> can this be a CodeableReference?</p>",
        "id": 185921551,
        "sender_full_name": "Jose Costa Teixeira",
        "timestamp": 1579272409
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Use Reference.display</p>",
        "id": 185922476,
        "sender_full_name": "Michele Mottini",
        "timestamp": 1579273131
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>How? With an embedded Location?</p>",
        "id": 185922520,
        "sender_full_name": "Jose Costa Teixeira",
        "timestamp": 1579273177
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>that is what I'd simplify</p>",
        "id": 185922539,
        "sender_full_name": "Jose Costa Teixeira",
        "timestamp": 1579273193
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>No embedded location - just populate only the <code>display</code> element of the Location reference (that is a pretty common thing to do)</p>",
        "id": 185922696,
        "sender_full_name": "Michele Mottini",
        "timestamp": 1579273267
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>ah ok. sorry, you are right.</p>",
        "id": 185922757,
        "sender_full_name": "Jose Costa Teixeira",
        "timestamp": 1579273321
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'd still prefer CodeableReference.</p>",
        "id": 185922813,
        "sender_full_name": "Jose Costa Teixeira",
        "timestamp": 1579273340
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>things like \"at home\", \"at work\" are good candidates for master data</p>",
        "id": 185922878,
        "sender_full_name": "Jose Costa Teixeira",
        "timestamp": 1579273395
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yes - it just requires adding that to the spec and then switching to a new version of FHIR</p>",
        "id": 185922995,
        "sender_full_name": "Michele Mottini",
        "timestamp": 1579273457
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>My goal is indeed to get feedback on that change before creating a Jira ticket</p>",
        "id": 185923177,
        "sender_full_name": "Jose Costa Teixeira",
        "timestamp": 1579273576
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>My feedback would be not to change it - there is an OK way to solve that problem with the current specs</p>",
        "id": 185923664,
        "sender_full_name": "Michele Mottini",
        "timestamp": 1579273892
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If location \"home\" is a code...?</p>",
        "id": 185925142,
        "sender_full_name": "Jose Costa Teixeira",
        "timestamp": 1579274805
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Having it coded allows for a constrained vocabulary of location types.  This would be a place where CodeableReference could make sense.  A change request is probably reasonable.</p>",
